S1901M.message: Hi everyone!
Hi Russia! Good luck this game, and let me know if you'd like to work together on anything.
Hey Italy! Any chance you're willing to do a lepanto and take out Turkey early?
Hello Austria! I'd very much like to work with you this game if you're interested. I think the AI is the strongest alliance on the board, and if you're down to make it work, I'm game to play it!

Hi England,
How are you feeling about the game? Any interest in an alliance?
Hi Turkey! Good luck this game, and let me know if there's anything I can do for you.

Hi Austria,
Looking forward to playing with you. I'm a big fan of the Austria/germany alliance. What do you think?
I'd love to make an AI work and Turkey is by far our strongest neighbor statistically so it would make sense.

Hello France! I'd love to have peace between us. I have no desire to come west as Italy in the early game, and it'd be great to not have to worry about a fleet build in Marseilles. In return, I'll stay out of your hair so you can focus on the west. Thoughts?

Hi Russia,
I'm hoping that we can have a peaceful border and both be successful in our respective spheres of influence. What do you say to keeping Prussia and Silesia as a DMZ?
Hey Russia, best of luck! Do you want to bounce in Galicia to keep things safe?
Good afternoon! How're the Balkans today?

Hi France,
I'm hoping we can work together this game. What are your thoughts on Belgium?
Hey Turkey, best of luck! Any interest in going hard against Russia early with me?

Hello Turkey! I think the IT is a really interesting alliance to play because no one ever sees it coming, and it's unexpected. My biggest problem is that I don't have many good opening options, so I'd love to work with you if you're game!
Sounds good to me!
Hey Germany! I am feeling pretty good, are you? What are you thinking for an alliance?

Hi Italy,
Can we keep Tyrolia empty? I'll stay out of it if you do.
Hey Germany, best of luck! I'd be interested in that. Any interest in maybe bouncing Russia from Sweden?
Hey France! Pretty standard so far. You?

Hi Turkey,
Looking forward to a fun game. If you want to discuss anything at all, let me know. I can't help you now, but maybe we can work together in the future.
Hello Russia! I find that R/I is one of the most underplayed alliances on the board, and if you're down to try to make it work, I'm game. Together, we can keep Austria and Turkey in check. Thoughts?
Hi Italy! Good luck this game. Let me know if I can help with anything.
I would very much like to have Belgium if you don't mind too terribly. Then again, I could be persuaded to give it up later in exchange for preferential gains in the UK.
In terms of specifics, what are your thoughts on Belgium?
Sure, what are your thoughts with Sweden?
Hello Germany! I'm happy to leave Tyrolia empty if you do too. I have no desire to go north or west as Italy in the early game, and if you stay out of Tyrolia, I'll stay out of your hair.
Hi Austria! Good luck this game. I don't think we have a ton to talk about right now, but let me know if I can be of service.
In terms of specifics, can we keep Burgundy empty?
Sure.
Thanks England! I'll be sure to do that. Best of luck to you as well!
Just getting started but I'm optimistic!
What are your thoughts on Sweden?
What are your thoughts on Italy?
Thanks England, good luck to you as well!
To be clear, I'm opening to Apulia and holding Venice, which is the most neutral and non-threatening set of opening moves I have as Italy haha
Hi France! Do you mind if we DMZ the channel?
Of course, as long as we can keep Ruhr empty as well

I'm going to have to see what happens in my triangle before I can commit to anything. I think it's in both of our interests for the three of us (you, me, Italy) to keep the center safe, so if Italy does anything weird like go to Tyrolia, we can always team up to repel him.
Italy seems like he'd be willing to do an attack on Turkey with us if we wanted. Do you have any opinion on Turkey?
To be clear, I'm opening to Apulia and holding Venice, which is the most neutral and non-threatening set of opening moves I have as Italy.
What are your thoughts on the three of us (you, me, Austria) keeping the center safe? That way, none of us are vulnerable to the outer powers.
Also! Let me know what you're thinking in terms of an opening. As England, I'm generally interested in allying with France over Germany, so let me know.
I like the idea of a central alliance - if Austria is game as well, I'm 100% game to go for that.

Hey England,

Good luck to you too!

What are your plans for Norway? I'm hoping to avoid the army moving over there.
I would support you into Rumania in the fall if you opened to Armenia
One note: Austria has been talking to me about containing Russia. If I can help to do that, it might be helpful for you. In exchange, I'd just ask that you keep it to yourself. Is that okay with you?
Sounds like a plan. You gonna Lapanto?
Sorry, didn't see your message. Do you have a specific division of Belgium in mind?
For what it's worth, I don't think France is opening to the Channel, at least from what he's told me.
Not yet
Also, I think I'll be bouncing Russia in Galicia to keep it safe
I don't plan on moving an army to Norway if we can agree on how to divide it up.
Are you planning on going hard on Russia or playing more of a western game?

One other thing: I'm reaching out to Turkey, and trying to gently let him know that if he wants to ally with you against Russia, I'll have your back on that. In exchange, I'd just ask that you keep it to yourself, and he won't get tipped off. What do you think?
Thanks for the tip!

A wintegreen is always fun. What are you thinking?

Sneaking Trie?
Italy seems potentially interested in attacking Turkey. I'm skeptical but that'd be great for you if he did.
To be blunt, it depends on how my triangle looks. I'm not saying no or yes, but I need to evaluate my position before I can make any commitments.
For what it's worth, Russia sounds like he is opening south. If you want to try to take advantage of that, feel free.
I'd feel fine DMZing the channel! I could certainly be persuaded into smacking the Germans.

I'm not planning on snaking Trieste - as Italy, I really have no choice but to play a boring, neutral opening. I'm happy to open against Austria in 1902 or Spring 1903, depending on how things go this phase.
For what it's worth, Russia sounds like he is opening south, which may open up the south for you. But don't quote me on that.
Are you thinking more of an E/G or G/F? Just trying to get a read on the west.
Italy has expressed interest in a central alliance, which I like.
To be clear, I'm opening neutral - Venice will hold, Rome will go to Apulia, and Naples will go to Ionian.
It's probably one of Italy's safest options
I'm just trying to figure out if you, me, and Italy are all on the same page. That will let us focus our resources on the outer powers and not each other.
And for what it's worth, I don't know. As England, I like to sort of feel the board out and see who seems friendlier. What about you?
I think if you play more of a western game we might be able to help each other with Russia mid-game
What do you think about a pink, red, and gold board?
To be clear, I'm opening neutral - Rome will go to Apulia, Venice will hold, and Naples will go to Ionian.
I really just want to open in the most neutral way possible as Italy - I can't afford to do anything crazy in the early game haha
Also! For what it's worth, Russia sounds like he is opening south, which might open up the north for us if we want to work together on Russia.
Specifically, I'll stay out of Tyrolia if you do.
I don't think we'll have a ton to talk about this phase, just as a heads up, I'll be bouncing Russia in Galicia
I understand that. I hope you'd also consider my side too. If I get squeezed, you probably don't want me collapsing first and letting the east resolve before the west.
Also! For what it's worth, Russia sounds like he is opening south, which might open up the south for you.

Let's keep Burgundy and Ruhr empty, but I think I'm going to need to move through Ruhr in the first turn. I don't want to spook you, and I can't really move the Munich army anywhere else. Does that work for you?
I've been getting a bunch of requests to Lepanto, so I'm trying to keep my options open with this opening - if you want to work together in 1902, I'll be down to try to get you into Greece.
I mean, maybe Russia isn't, but that's what he said. He also didn't seem super enthused about Scandinavia, so, who knows.
I'd be willing to support you in from Serbia

Also, Germany is offering a central alliance - I'm game for that if you are. If so, I'll go for a normal Lepanto against Turkey, though I'll be happy to try to help you into Greece if you let me take it in 1902.
That is, I'd be interested in a pink, red, and gold board.
I'm thinking I'm going to be the odd one out of the western triangle, so I want to keep my back safe.
You might be able to swing Germany for that, too.
If you went hard after France, I think Italy would be happy to send a few units west with you, given that he doesn't seem interested in attacking me.
What are your thoughts on all that?

Hi Turkey! I'd like to wish you luck.

Want to bounce in Black?
How's the West looking?
How do you want to handle Belgium?
Are you thinking more of an E/F or an E/G?
How's the west looking?
A strong France is good for an Austria and vice versa.
I think it would probably be easiest for you to have Sweden, and for me to have Belgium. Is that something you could agree to?
Have you talked to Austria?
I'd also be interested in your thoughts on Germany?
Does that interest you?
One thing: Austria is looking for allies to help him contain you. I'm not inclined to do that, but you should be careful.
What does that division look like to you? Is there anything to divide but Norway and Sweden?
I just think it's the safest option for you given that you'll probably bounce in the Black Sea in 1901
To be clear, I'm opening to Apulia and holding Venice, which is the most neutral and non-threatening set of opening moves I have as Italy
Has Austria seemed friendly?
Do you have a strong preference?
Also, this will allow me to help you diplomatically by getting Austria and Russia fighting. That's what I've tried to do, but it doesn't help when they aren't fighting.
I'm leaning toward FG, but if England talks well enough I could go FE
I don't really have a strong opinion on which of Germany or France you should side with, though
Austria offered to bounce in Gal. I said sure. I don't know why he's paranoid?
I'm trying to convince the Germans to let me walk in.
One other thing: I'm trying to encourage Turkey and Russia to fight. That will let us be free to deal with the outer powers, without worrying about them allying against us.
Are you planning to let Russia have Sweden?
I know most Turkey players are hesitant to do that, but I think it's important to cripple Russia early
If you want to move aggressively against Germany, I can follow you with fleets, but it's up to you.
As long as I get Belgium, that'd be fine.

I think it depends on how everyone else moves, but if everyone else is fighting in the first turn, I'm happy to help you into Belgium. That said, I'd much prefer to get your support into Sweden in exchange. Is that okay?
Are you planning on moving to Galicia?
If you agree to open to Armenia I will bounce Russia in Galicia, and then in the fall we can see if Russia opens south or north
Have you talked to France?
Let me know if you need anything!
Also! Let me know how you're feeling about Russia, generally.
For example, if Russia allies with Austria, it's bad news for you.
Italy sounds like he's on board for a central alliance, and I'm on board as well
I have heard friendly words from both Austria and Italy, and I always like to see Turkey do well.
I'm all about playing aggressive
Italy sounds pretty interested in opening traditionally, which isn't great for you, but he also didn't sound interested in a Lepanto.
Also, how are things with England? I haven't gotten too much out of him.

Yes, Austria asked to bounce and I said sure.

Chicago players sneak Trieste all the time to get the extra fleet. Just a thought.
For what it's worth, France has seemed to lean towards allying with you
Also, Russia has told me he is opening south. I don't know if that's true - I imagine that would involve a move to the Black Sea, but I thought I'd let you know.
Germany and England are both clamoring for my assistance.
It would be, I think, easiest if I took Norway with a fleet and you took Sweden with a fleet. Then if you don't build in St P, I'd be happy to DMZ both, or add other conditions.
England seems interested in a pink, red, and gold board, if that helps at all
Are you and France Dmzing the channel? I hope you guys can work together!
If you build anything in St P, I'd be very unhappy.
I haven't either.
Austria seemed friendly to me too, but I don't have much reason to expect a lot of help from Austria early on, so I'm not expecting anything crazy from him.
Have you had any productive discussions with England? I'm trying to get a read on him.
If we were to do a Wintergreen, when would you move against Austria and how would you want to split Turkey/Austria?
Let me know if that helps your planning!
For what it's worth, Russia has told me that he is going south - but I don't know if that means a move to Galicia.

One other thing: It sounds like Russia is going to go south. That's good for us (for now), but once he takes care of Austria and Turkey, he's going to want to move west. I'd like to avoid that if we can.
Let me know what you think!
Doesn't surprise me much
Are you and England Dmzing the channel?
Do you want me to advocate for a E/F or a G/F?
I'd like to keep Austria safe. I think it's in our mutual interests for him to do well.
I do think that given that Russia sounds like he is opening south, we could quickly move against Germany and get both of us two builds in 1901.
Would building A StP be offensive if I don't get Swe in 1901?
If I get my fleet into Greece we could have Turkey on the ropes immediately
To be clear, I'm planning on going for a neutral opening, which I don't think commits me anywhere. What have you heard from Turkey?
Absolutely. We should try to take the English down as fast as possible.
Specifically, if he goes to the Channel, we should team up against him.
If you think you might want to work together against Germany, let me know.
Seems like Russia is opening south for what it's worth, which is good for you

Also, I think we should definitely encourage Russia and Turkey to fight each other. It's in our interest to have them fighting so that you and I can work together in the midgame - if they're allied, you and I are next on the list!
Potentially, depending on what Germany does.
And just to be clear, a fleet build in Marseilles is an automatic war declaration against me.
Definitely. That'd be a huge red flag.
It's going to be hard to get a read on him if he never responds to my messages, though.

I think the best move for Russia in 1901 is to bounce BLA with turkey and move Moscow to Ukraine. Then in the fall you can take Rumania with your army in Ukraine and build another fleet in Sevastopol, or an army if you want to move north
That's the plan atm
My hope is to get you into Sweden while I move against Germany. Then, you can support me to Denmark, and I can support you to Berlin.
Turkey has been pretty quiet - what's he been telling you?

Sorry, the message didn't come through before I asked the question.

In regards to Germany, I have to see what happens with the bounce. If it looks like he's going to bounce me and I need the space, I'm not opposed to letting him take it while I move to Bal and you move to Den
One other thing: If you attack Austria, I think it's going to mean bad things for me. I don't want to get involved in the east.
I think the key to this board is an E/F for now, and we can pivot to an I/A/F midgame if it looks like it's working.

Basically, if Russia and Austria ally, I want you to ally with Austria and contain Russia. That's in my interests too. In return, I want to keep Austria safe in the south, which means that if he moves north, you'll be in his way. It's good for you if the two of them fight.
DMZing the channel I mean, not building a fleet in MARS

What's the press in the west like? I'd really like to keep an eye on F Mar if that happens - I don't think a France that's fighting you is a great player in the long run, so that's probably what he'll do if you guys aren't Dmzing the channel
Just to be clear, I'm trying to play the friendly "I'm interested in containing Russia" card, but without actually threatening you.
Yeah, at this point I might take that as hostile intent, if I were you
I am also trying to get Turkey to open against Russia; maybe you can help with that.
I'm not sure I trust England. He asked me how to divide the north??? There's two centers. Why ask that?
Another important thing: You're a naturally fleet-based power. That means your growth is going to be slower than mine. As a result, I'll need you to support me into Scs.
I think an EF would work best at the moment
I have heard nothing. Has Turkey messaged you?

F1901M.message: Looks like Turkey and Russia are fighting, which is great for us!
That looks more like an E/G, which isn't great for you
France is moving his fleet to Picardy, which seems to indicate that he trusts you more than Germany?
Well, it looks like you were right about Russia, although I was wrong about Turkey.
One suggestion: You could move to Barents Sea and convoy to Norway. That would be devastating to Russia. I could go to Ska, and support you in the next turn.
The lack of a move into the Channel is encouraging, at least
Looks like you're going after Russia. I'd love to help, but there's not a ton I can do to help in 1901 haha
Did you mean that the other way around?
You need England or Germany to flip on the other
Okay, so you get Belgium, I get Holland. That's fair.
Would you prefer if I convoyed to Tunis or went for a regular Lepanto?
Yes, sorry, I meant Belgium.
I don't want to see a France with three builds early. If you work with Germany you can potentially keep France from getting Belgium
Oof, it looks like you're going to have your hands full with Turkey!
That's an interesting move from Turkey.
Indeed. It's looking like Russia's coming for you btw.
Great opening for you.
I don't want to see France get three builds. I think you and England should work together to bounce him in Belgium
What do you think?
Sounds like a plan!
The E/F looks pretty strong so far, which isn't great for you, but England could be convinced to flip on France with you
I guess that didn't work out?
The boat is a really, really odd play. That leaves him totally open to Italy
I think convoy to Tunis is preferred, and then you can build F Naples and move Nap-ion and Ion-east Med in the spring, and then you can convoy into Syria or Smyrna in the fall
We should definitely try to prevent it. My impression is that England isn't a great communicator. Have you had much press with him?

Concerning opening from Germany

Nice move to Armenia! That's amazing.

I think I have the pick of the litter!
Nice move to Armenia!
What are your thoughts on Germany and France?

Germany and England are both falling over themselves to be my friend
Things look good for you! Are you planning on convoying to Norway?
I think we could cripple Turkey pretty quickly if you're on board
No idea yet. Are you trying a Lepanto?
That's an interesting opening from Turkey. Have you had press with him? He's been totally silent.
Are you thinking about moving Norwegian to Barents? I don't love that Russia gets a build from Sweden, but we don't want him collapsing too quickly...

Hey France.

What are your thoughts on the west? I can't get a read on England and Germany.

Howdy Russia! Looks like you're going after Austria first, but that entry into the Black Sea is pretty fortuitous.

As for things in the West, I think both England and Germany are banking on my help.
Would you be willing to support me into Rum?
Yeah, Turkey's opening is odd. Also, zero press from Turkey
It's a fleet not an army. Worst case scenario he takes Sev. He can't go Mos with that.
Well, them being in Armenia is no problem at all for you so long as you hold the Black Sea. But I wouldn't be surprised if they're banking on being able to build in ANK by bouncing you there.
I think you stand to benefit the most. He can't stop a lepanto
What're your thoughts?
I would like to still bounce in Gal. Is that ok? Turkey is in a tough place. I'd rather not squabble with you. Do you think we can work together?
Thanks, I was having a little technical difficulty on my end so sorry about the non response
I am good to move against Russia as it seems like they're pushing south towards me
Have you heard anything from Austria? He asked to not bounce in Gal and I haven't heard anything since.

What are your plans with the army?

Want to put it in Den?

Sorry was having some tech difficulties to start so I missed that message

Mobile device moves, didn't want to stall out and was trying to figure everything out
What are your thoughts in the east?

Let's avoid England bouncing you in Belgium. Instead, I'll move Den -> Ska, Kiel -> Den, Ruhr -> Hol. That will give me Sweden next year. You can build two fleets this turn, which is a really good start.
Yeah - the real wild card here is whether Turkey goes for Greece. Are you going to try to block him?
Has Turkey sent you any press?
Yup! How are things going with Austria?
I'm still trying to get turkey to go after Russia
Turkey messaged me - he said "had some tech difficulties"
I don't know. Maybe a triple.

We need to tlak about Ank.

You need to get to Smyrna

England and Austria seem like they hate me?
